    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "What AI tools support this skill?",
        "answer": "This skill works with Claude, Claude Code, and Codex. It uses MCP tools from claude-flow for agent coordination."
      },
      {
        "question": "Does this skill deploy to any hosting platform?",
        "answer": "No. The skill orchestrates agents but requires your own deployment scripts. The deploy.sh script handles platform-specific deployment."
      },
      {
        "question": "How does rollback work?",
        "answer": "The skill monitors health metrics during deployment. If error rate exceeds thresholds, it triggers rollback to the previous version using rollback.sh."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is my repository data safe?",
        "answer": "Yes. This skill only coordinates agents that follow your existing workflows. No data is sent to external services beyond your configured deployment targets."
      },
      {
        "question": "What if tests fail during release?",
        "answer": "Any validation test failure blocks the release. The skill documents the failure and waits for human investigation before retry or abort."
      },
      {
        "question": "How is this different from GitHub Actions?",
        "answer": "This skill coordinates AI agents that can make decisions and adapt workflows. GitHub Actions runs predefined scripts. They can work together."
      }
